│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The issue is that SCCP (Sparse Conditional Constant Propagation) is incorrectly folding a vector fcmp instruction with denormal inputs when the function has "denormal-fp-math"="ieee,dynamic" attribute. The  │
│ first element of the vector contains a denormal value (0x8000000000000 = 2^-1022 in double precision), while the second element is 1.0. The comparison is against zeroinitializer (both elements are 0.0).     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ For FCMP_UNE (unordered or not equal):                                                                                                                                                                         │
│ - First element: denormal != 0.0 should be true                                                                                                                                                                │
│ - Second element: 1.0 != 0.0 should be true                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ However, the problem is that with "dynamic" denormal handling, the actual runtime behavior depends on the current floating-point control register state, which determines whether denormals are flushed to     │
│ zero or treated normally. When denormals are flushed to zero, the first comparison would be 0.0 != 0.0 = false.                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The SCCP pass is incorrectly assuming that the denormal will always be treated as a normal value (IEEE mode) and folding it to <true, true>, but with dynamic denormal handling, this is not guaranteed at     │
│ compile time.                                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:                                                                                                                                                                                      │
